  "title": "Chemical Clean Processor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Chemically clean parts, often engine components, to remove coatings, rust, paint, carbon, and grease before inspection or repair (like FPI).</li><li>Follow specific operation sheets, manuals, and SPOP (Standard Process Operating Procedure) specifications for each job.</li><li>Add chemicals to tanks, monitor solution concentrations (pH, temperature), test solutions, and manage waste, ensuring material reactivity knowledge.</li><li>Operate and monitor cleaning line equipment, pumps, filters, and tanks, assisting maintenance as needed.</li><li> Verify part numbers, check for correct processes, identify faulty operations, and maintain meticulous records/paperwork.</li><li>Wear protective gear (gloves, masks, suits) and maintain a clean, safe work area.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min GCE ‘O’ level and above</li><li>Min 1 year of experience in Aerospace / Manufacturing Industry</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call<strong> </strong><a href=\"tel:+(65)%C2%A06513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>+(65) 6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
